[30;1m865 | [0m[35m<ul class="simple">[0m
[30;1m866 | [0m[35m<li>Major API change: DB URI parser was changed to use urllib.split*() and[0m
[30;1m867 | [0m[35munquote(). This means any username/password/path are allowed in DB[0m
[30;1m868 | [0m[35mURIs if they are properly %-encoded, and DB URIs are automatically[0m
[30;1m869 | [0m[35munquoted.</li>[0m

[30;1m631 | [0m[35m<p>There are several factors when considering the efficiency of this[0m
[30;1m632 | [0m[35mkind of batching, and it depends very much how the batching is[0m
[30;1m633 | [0m[35mbeing used.  Consider a web application where you are showing an[0m
[30;1m634 | [0m[35maverage of 100 results, 10 at a time, and the results are ordered[0m

[30;1m513 | [0m[35m------------[0m
[30;1m514 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m515 | [0m[35mBy default SQLObject sends an ``UPDATE`` to the database for every[0m
[30;1m516 | [0m[35mattribute you set, or every time you call ``.set()``.  If you want to[0m
[30;1m517 | [0m[35mavoid this many updates, add ``lazyUpdate = True`` to your class `sqlmeta[0m
[30;1m518 | [0m[35mdefinition`_.[0m
[30;1m519 | [0m[35m[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m893[0m[34m of [0m[33m1412[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000600[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Windows[0m
  Severity: [36mModerate[0m, Confidence: [36mLow[0m
  Filename: [33m/SQLObject-3.13.0/docs/News.rst[0m
   Pattern: [32m\s(advpack\.dll|appvlp|at|atbroker|bash|bginfo|bitsadmin|cdb|certutil|cl_invocation\.ps1|cl_mutexverifiers\.ps1|cmd|cmdkey|cmstp|comsvcs\.dll|control|csc|cscript|csi|devtoolslauncher|dfsvc|diskshadow|dnscmd|dnx|dotnet|dxcap|esentutl|eventvwr|excel|expand|extexport|extrac32|findstr|forfiles|ftp|gfxdownloadwrapper|gpscript|hh|ie4uinit|ieadvpack\.dll|ieaframe\.dll|ic|infdefaultinstall|installutil|jsc|makecab|manage-bde\.wsf|mavinject|mftrace|microsoft\.workflow\.compiler|mmc|msbuild|msconfig|msdeploy|msdt|mshta|mshtml\.dll|msc|msxsl|netsh|odbcconf|pcalua|pcwrun|pcwutl\.dll|pester\.bat|powerpnt|presentationhost|pubprn\.vbs|rcsi|reg|regasm|regedit|register-cimprovider|regsvcs|regsvr32|rpcping|rundll32|runonce|runscripthelper|sc|schtasks|scriptrunner|setupapi\.dll|shdocvw\.dll|shell32\.dll|slmgr\.vbs|sqldumper|sqlps|sqltoolsps|squirrel|syncappvpublishingserver|syncappvpublishingserver\.vbs|syssetup\.dll|te|tracker|tttracer|update|url\.dll|verclsid|vsjitdebugger|wab|winrm\.vbs|winword|wmic|wscript|wsl|wsreset|xwizard|zipfldr\.dll)\s[0m
[30;1m141 | [0m[35m  ``SQLite`` requires different connections per thread so[0m
[30;1m142 | [0m[35m  ``SQLiteConnection`` creates and stores a connection per thread.[0m
[30;1m143 | [0m[35m  When a thread finishes its connections should be closed.[0m
[30;1m144 | [0m[35m  But if a program doesn't cooperate and doesn't close connections at[0m
[30;1m145 | [0m[35m  the end of a thread SQLObject leaks memory as connection objects are[0m
[30;1m146 | [0m[35m  stuck in ``SQLiteConnection``. On Linux the leak is negligible as[0m
[30;1m147 | [0m[35m  Linux reuses thread IDs so new connections replace old ones and old[0m
[30;1m148 | [0m[35m  connections are garbage collected. But Windows doesn't reuse thread[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m1024[0m[34m of [0m[33m1412[0m[31m ]--[0m

[30;1m464 | [0m[35mWhen you reload a module, new classes are created, and they take over[0m
[30;1m465 | [0m[35mthe names in the module.[0m
[30;1m466 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m467 | [0m[35mSQLObject, however, doesn't search the names in a module to find a[0m
[30;1m468 | [0m[35mclass.  When you say ``ForeignKey('SomeClass')``, SQLObject looks for[0m
[30;1m469 | [0m[35many SQLObject subclass anywhere with the name ``SomeClass``.  This is[0m
[30;1m470 | [0m[35mto avoid problems with circular imports and circular dependencies, as[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m1025[0m[34m of [0m[33m1412[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000610[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Linux[0m

[30;1m172 | [0m[35mDaniel Savard has implemented inheritance for SQLObject. In `terms of[0m
[30;1m173 | [0m[35mORM`_ this is a kind of vertical inheritance. The only difference is[0m
[30;1m174 | [0m[35mthat objects reference their leaves, not parents. Links to parents are[0m
[30;1m175 | [0m[35mreconstructed at run-time using the hierarchy of Python classes.[0m
[30;1m176 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m177 | [0m[35m.. _`terms of ORM`: https://cayenne.apache.org/docs/3.0/modeling-inheritance.html[0m
[30;1m178 | [0m[35m[0m
